abstract: White House Memo; Vice Pres Joseph R Biden Jr's assertiveness during diplomatic trip to Ukraine signals that he is returning to full-throated form as final year of his term approaches; follows yearlong quiet period during which Biden mourned death of his son and declined bid for presidency in 2016.
lead_paragraph: Having decided not to run for president, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has returned full-time to his duties as the nation’s second-highest official with ambitions to get as much done as he can in the 13 months he has left.

headline.main: Finding Voice Again, Joe Biden Sees Time Left to Make a Difference
headline.print_headline: Finding Voice Again, Biden Sees Time Left to Make a Difference
